    "asOf": "2009-05-04",
    "date": "2009-05-22T20:43:32Z",
    "text": "Teacher Tax Credit Act of 2009 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow an eligible educator an annual $2,000 tax credit. Defines: (1) \"eligible educator\" as an individual who is a kindergarten through grade 12 teacher, instructor, counselor, principal, or aide in an eligible elementary or secondary school for at least 900 hours during a school year; and (2) \"eligible elementary or secondary school\" as a school that is eligible for schoolwide assistance under the Elementary and Secondary Education Act of 1965."
